        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 4:42PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 441 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cement City, or 11 miles south of Jackson, moving northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brooklyn...            Grass Lake...          Vandercook Lake...
Napoleon...            Norvell...             Clark Lake...
Lake Columbia...       Oak Point...           Sunset Beach...
Liberty...             Michigan Center...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
